{
  "texts": [
    "The integration and enhancement of multi-level features can significantly enhance model performance.",
    "Therefore, we investigate the effectiveness of feature fusion strategies in polyp segmentation models.",
    "Traditional modelsEarly works primarily relied on manually designed features, such as color, texture, and shape, and then employed traditional machine learning techniques for heuristic modeling.",
    "For instance, Yao et al. [76] proposed an automatic polyp segmentation method that combines knowledge-guided intensity adjustment, fuzzy c-means clustering, and deformable models.",
    "Lu et al. [77] proposed a three-stage probabilistic binary classification method that integrates low-level and mid-level information to segment polyps in 3D CT colonography."
  ]
}